#. type: multicols*
#: sections/ai_rules.tex:6
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"{2}\n"
"  AI rules apply to Enemy Heroes and all Combat encounters, including those against Neutral Units, in \\textbf{Solo Campaigns} and \\textbf{Cooperative} Scenarios.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/ai_rules.tex:11
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  \\bigskip\n"
"  \\pagetarget{AI Units}{\\subheader{Combat against AI}}\n"
"  Foreword: these rules are intended to make fun challenging encounters, but still be simple enough to follow.\n"
"  You will likely find some loopholes which make the encounter too easy, but you may make AI behave more intellegently.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/ai_rules.tex:13
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid ""
#| "\\pagetarget{AI Units}{These rules} apply during Combat in \\textbf{Solo}\\index{Solo Mode} and \\textbf{Cooperative} Scenarios.\n"
#| "The rules for AI Unit placement during setup are described in \\pagelink{CombatAISetup}{Combat chapter}.\n"
#| "\n"
msgid ""
"  The rules for AI unit placement during setup are described in \\pagelink{CombatAISetup}{Combat section}.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
"\\pagetarget{AI Units}{Niniejsze zasady} obowiązują podczas Walki w trybach \\textbf{Solo}\\index{Tryb Solo} oraz \\textbf{Kooperacyjnym}.\n"
"Zasady rozmieszczania Jednostek AI podczas przygotowania są opisane w rozdziale \\pagelink{CombatAISetup}{Walka}.\n"
"\n"

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/ai_rules.tex:15
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid ""
#| "When Neutral enemies or AI Heroes activate a Unit, they follow a set of automatic instructions:\\par\n"
#| "\n"
msgid ""
"  When Neutral enemies or \\pagelink{AI Heroes}{AI Heroes} activate a unit, they follow a set of instructions:\\par\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
"Gdy Neutralni wrogowie lub Bohaterowie AI aktywują Jednostkę, wykonują polecenia:\\par\n"
"\n"

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/ai_rules.tex:18
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  \\begin{itemize}\n"
"    \\item If it is an AI Hero, draw and resolve the next \\pagelink{AI Deck}{AI card}.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/ai_rules.tex:21
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid ""
#| "\\begin{itemize}\n"
#| "  \\item Enemy Ground \\svg{unit_ground} and Flying \\svg{unit_flying} Units prioritize attacking Units of the \\textbf{same} tier.\n"
#| "  If this is impossible, they attack the Unit of a lower tier (in tier \\textbf{descending} order, down to bronze), and if that is also impossible, they attack the Unit of a higher tier (in tier \\textbf{ascending} order).\\par\n"
#| "\n"
msgid ""
"    \\item Enemy Ground \\svg{unit_ground} and Flying \\svg{unit_flying} units prioritize attacking units of the \\textbf{same} tier.\n"
"    If this is impossible, they attack the unit of a lower tier (in tier \\textbf{descending} order, down to bronze), and if that is also impossible, they attack the unit of a higher tier (in tier \\textbf{ascending} order).\\par\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
"\\begin{itemize}\n"
"  \\item Wrogie Jednostki Naziemne \\svg{unit_ground} oraz Latające \\svg{unit_flying} atakują w pierwszej kolejności Jednostki \\textbf{tego samego} poziomu.\n"
"  Jeśli jest to niemożliwe, atakują Jednostkę niższego poziomu (w \\textbf{malejącej} kolejności aż do brązowego), a jeśli i to jest niemożliwe, Jednostkę wyższego poziomu (w \\textbf{rosnącej} kolejności poziomów).\\par\n"
"\n"

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/ai_rules.tex:27
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid ""
#| "  \\textit{Example: \\svg{golden}\\svg{unit_ground} has this priority:\n"
#| "  \\svg{golden}\n"
#| "  - \\svg{silver}\n"
#| "  - \\svg{bronze}\n"
#| "  - \\svg{azure}.}\n"
#| "\n"
msgid ""
"    \\textit{Example: \\svg{golden}\\svg{unit_ground} has this priority:\n"
"    \\svg{golden}\n"
"    - \\svg{silver}\n"
"    - \\svg{bronze}\n"
"    - \\svg{azure}.}\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
"  \\textit{Przykład: \\svg{golden}\\svg{unit_ground} atakuje kolejno:\n"
"  \\svg{golden}\n"
"  - \\svg{silver}\n"
"  - \\svg{bronze}\n"
"  - \\svg{azure}.}\n"
"\n"

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/ai_rules.tex:30
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid ""
#| "  \\item Ranged \\svg{unit_ranged} Units prioritize attacking other Ranged \\svg{unit_ranged} Units of the same tier, then lower tier, and finally higher tier, using the same tier order as above.\n"
#| "  If there are no Ranged \\svg{unit_ranged} Units for them to target, they prioritize Ground \\svg{unit_ground} and Flying \\svg{unit_flying} Units in the same tier order.\\par\n"
#| "\n"
msgid ""
"    \\item Ranged \\svg{unit_ranged} units prioritize attacking other Ranged \\svg{unit_ranged} units of the same tier, then lower tier, and finally higher tier, using the same tier order as above.\n"
"    If there are no Ranged \\svg{unit_ranged} units for them to target, they prioritize Ground \\svg{unit_ground} and Flying \\svg{unit_flying} units in the same tier order.\\par\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
"  \\item Jednostki Strzelające \\svg{unit_ranged} atakują najpierw inne Jednostki Strzelające \\svg{unit_ranged} tego samego poziomu, potem niższego poziomu, a na końcu wyższego w takiej samej kolejności, jak opisano wyżej.\n"
"  Jeśli nie ma Jednostek Strzelających, które mogłyby być celem Ataku, najpierw atakują Jednostki Naziemne \\svg{unit_ground} oraz Latające \\svg{unit_flying} w tej samej kolejności poziomów.\\par\n"
"  \n"

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/ai_rules.tex:41
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid ""
#| "  \\textit{Example: \\svg{silver}\\svg{unit_ranged} has this priority:\n"
#| "  \\svg{silver}\\svg{unit_ranged}\n"
#| "  - \\svg{bronze}\\svg{unit_ranged}\n"
#| "  - \\svg{golden}\\svg{unit_ranged}\n"
#| "  - \\svg{azure}\\svg{unit_ranged}\n"
#| "  - \\svg{silver}\\svg{unit_ground}\\svg{unit_flying}\n"
#| "  - \\svg{bronze}\\svg{unit_ground}\\svg{unit_flying}\n"
#| "  - \\svg{golden}\\svg{unit_ground}\\svg{unit_flying}\n"
#| "  - \\svg{azure}\\svg{unit_ground}\\svg{unit_flying}.}\n"
#| "\\end{itemize}\n"
#| "\n"
msgid ""
"    \\textit{Example: \\svg{silver}\\svg{unit_ranged} has this priority:\n"
"    \\svg{silver}\\svg{unit_ranged}\n"
"    - \\svg{bronze}\\svg{unit_ranged}\n"
"    - \\svg{golden}\\svg{unit_ranged}\n"
"    - \\svg{azure}\\svg{unit_ranged}\n"
"    - \\svg{silver}\\svg{unit_ground}\\svg{unit_flying}\n"
"    - \\svg{bronze}\\svg{unit_ground}\\svg{unit_flying}\n"
"    - \\svg{golden}\\svg{unit_ground}\\svg{unit_flying}\n"
"    - \\svg{azure}\\svg{unit_ground}\\svg{unit_flying}.}\n"
"  \\end{itemize}\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
"  \\textit{Przykład: \\svg{silver}\\svg{unit_ranged} atakuje kolejno:\n"
"  \\svg{silver}\\svg{unit_ranged}\n"
"  - \\svg{bronze}\\svg{unit_ranged}\n"
"  - \\svg{golden}\\svg{unit_ranged}\n"
"  - \\svg{azure}\\svg{unit_ranged}\n"
"  - \\svg{silver}\\svg{unit_ground}\\svg{unit_flying}\n"
"  - \\svg{bronze}\\svg{unit_ground}\\svg{unit_flying}\n"
"  - \\svg{golden}\\svg{unit_ground}\\svg{unit_flying}\n"
"  - \\svg{azure}\\svg{unit_ground}\\svg{unit_flying}.}\n"
"\\end{itemize}\n"
"\n"

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/ai_rules.tex:44
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid ""
#| "In both cases, if there's more than one valid target, they attack the closest one.\n"
#| "If there's ever a tie between equally valid targets, the player chooses which Unit is attacked.\\par\n"
#| "\n"
msgid ""
"  In both cases, if there is more than one valid target, they attack the closest one.\n"
"  If there is ever a tie between equally valid targets, the player chooses which unit is attacked.\\par\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
"W obu przypadkach, jeśli jest więcej niż jeden możliwy cel, atakują najbliższy.\n"
"Jeśli wystąpi remis pomiędzy równorzędnymi celami, Gracz wybiera, która Jednostka jest atakowana.\\par\n"
"\n"

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/ai_rules.tex:46
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid ""
#| "Enemy Units cannot \\pagelink{Defend}{Defend} unless instructed to.\n"
#| "\n"
msgid ""
"  Enemy units cannot \\pagelink{Defend}{defend} unless instructed to.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
"Wrogie Jednostki nie mogą \\pagelink{Defend}{się bronić}, chyba że otrzymają takie polecenie.\n"
"\\vfill\n"

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/ai_rules.tex:52
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"  \\pagetarget{AI Siege}{\\subsection*{AI Siege}}\n"
"  When the Walls and Gate are mentioned in Combat preparation but no additional information on how to arrange them is given, arrange them as a human player would:\n"
"  place the Gate in front of the \\svg{unit_ground} unit with the highest \\svg{initiative}.\n"
"  By default, the units do not attack the Walls -- they would rather fly over them to attack their target or move towards it through the Gate.\n"
"  If it is not possible, they take a \\pagelink{Defend}{Defend} Action.\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: multicols*
#: sections/ai_rules.tex:55
#, fuzzy, no-wrap
#| msgid ""
#| "\\vspace{1em}\n"
#| "\\note{9}{In a siege against AI, the Arrow Tower follows the priority-rules like a Silver \\svg{silver} Unit. But if there are many valid targets, it cannot attack the nearest one, so it will attack the one that is closest to perishing (the smallest difference between \\svg{health_points-yellow} and current \\svg{damage-yellow}).}\n"
#| "\n"
msgid ""
"  The \\pagelink{Walls}{Arrow Tower} is treated like a Silver \\svg{silver}\\svg{unit_ranged} unit.\n"
"  However, if it has multiple equally valid targets to attack, it will attack the one with the least health remaining (the smallest difference between \\svg{health_points} and current \\svg{damage}).\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
"\\vspace{1em}\n"
"\\note{9}{W oblężeniu przeciwko AI Wieża Łucznicza atakuje jak Srebrna \\svg{silver} Jednostka. Jeśli jest więcej niż jeden możliwy cel, nie może atakować najbliższego, więc zaatakuje ten, który jest najbliżej śmierci (najmniejsza różnica między \\svg{health_points-yellow} a obecnymi \\svg{damage-yellow}).}\n"
"\n"

